ce:section.ce:para:
To enhance QC solubility and bioavailability, the CS/HNTs/GQDs nanocarrier was employed for QC delivery, and the impact of HNTs nanoparticles on its LE and EE values was also assessed using equations (1) and (2). For CS/GQDs nanocomposites, LE and EE values were 32.0 % and 69.0 %, respectively, increasing to 44.25 % and 85.5 % upon HNTs addition (Table 1
                           ). This phenomenon can be attributed to the augmented hydrogen bonding interactions between the nanocomposite and QC after introducing HNTs into the CS/GQDs nanocomposite, leading to enhanced QC absorption onto the nanocomposite and its higher entrapment within the CS network. Table 2
                            presents QC LE and EE values for various delivery systems reported in the literature. According to this table, the highest drug loading percentage is associated with QC/caseinate/kappa-carrageenan-coated zein (75.7 %), [49] while the highest drug encapsulation efficiency is observed for QC/Fe2O3/CS/montmorillonite (94 %).[5] The drug encapsulation efficiency obtained for CS/HNTs/GQDs in this work is near the highest reported value.
